#week-title("Three", "Setting Up the Laboratory & The First Herb")

=== Core Teaching

The laboratory is the alchemist's outer sanctuary. It need not be elaborate.
What it must be is *clean, orderly, consistently maintained,* and treated with the
same seriousness as an inner practice space. The laboratory and the meditation space
are not two separate things — they are the same Work operating through two hands.

The minimum equipment for beginning spagyric work is modest: a few glass flasks,
a heating source capable of gentle sustained warmth, a condenser for distillation,
a mortar and pestle, an earthenware or porcelain dish for calcination, dark glass
storage bottles. The most important piece of equipment is not glass or metal —
it is *attention*.

*The Four Degrees of Fire.* The ancients distinguished four degrees of fire, each
appropriate to different operations:

